# Auth Routes

All authentication UI lives under **`src/routes/(public)/auth/`** — never at the route root or outside `(public)/auth/`.

| Page | Path |
|------|------|
| Login | `/auth/login` |
| Sign up | `/auth/signup` |
| Forgot password | `/auth/forget-password` |
| Reset password | `/auth/reset-password` |
| OTP / verification code | `/auth/otp` |
| Verification success | `/auth/verification-success` |
| Accept invite | `/auth/accept-invite` |
| Sign out (POST) | `/auth/logout` |

Use path constants from [`src/lib/constants/auth-routes.ts`](src/lib/constants/auth-routes.ts).

Rules:

- **No** `/login`, `/signup`, or `/logout` at the routes root (legacy redirects only)
- Auth pages use the shared `(public)/auth/+layout.svelte` shell
- Forms follow [`forms-layout.mdc`](forms-layout.mdc) (card + `form-table` + `form-actions`)
- Unauthenticated guards redirect to `/auth/login?redirectTo=…`
- Better Auth API stays at `/api/auth/*` (hooks) — only **pages** use `/auth/*`
- Email sign-up sends an OTP via Better Auth `emailOTP` plugin; user completes verification at `/auth/otp`
- Admin invites use `/auth/accept-invite?token=…` (password only, no OTP)
- Configure SMTP env vars for production email delivery (see `.env.example`)

